BT /F2 18.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 50.00 798.00 Tm (myMatrixClock2 App Summary) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 50.00 781.00 Tm (One-page repo-based brief) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 745.00 Tm (What It Is) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 730.00 Tm (A PlatformIO/Arduino firmware project for a Teensy-based RGB LED matrix clock that reads time from a DS1307 RTC) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 718.50 Tm (and renders the current time, date, and DST status with SmartMatrix.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 707.00 Tm (Repo evidence shows a HUB75 SmartMatrix display stack, serial time-setting, automatic Central European DST handling,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 695.50 Tm (and day/night brightness switching.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 676.00 Tm (Who It's For) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 661.00 Tm (Primary persona: a hobbyist/maker building a Teensy-powered LED matrix clock and comfortable using PlatformIO, a) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 649.50 Tm (serial monitor, and RTC-backed embedded hardware.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 630.00 Tm (What It Does) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 615.00 Tm (- Shows hour:minute on the matrix using SmartMatrix fonts and double-buffered drawing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 603.50 Tm (- Displays the day/month date plus a DST and weekday status line.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 592.00 Tm (- Reads current time from a DS1307 RTC and syncs the Time library from that source.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 580.50 Tm (- Accepts serial input in YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS format to validate and set the RTC.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 569.00 Tm (- Applies Central European daylight-saving rules in firmware for display hour adjustment.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 557.50 Tm (- Switches between day brightness 10 and night brightness 0 based on display hour.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 546.00 Tm (- Shows a startup message immediately, then prompts on serial for time-set input.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 526.50 Tm (How It Works) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 511.50 Tm (- Runtime target: PlatformIO env `teensy31` with the Arduino framework.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 500.00 Tm (- Display path: firmware draws into a SmartMatrix indexed layer and swaps buffers to a configured 32x32 HUB75 panel.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 488.50 Tm (- Time path: DS1307 RTC -> Time library sync provider -> `loop\(\)` reads RTC once per second -> DST/brightness rules) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 477.00 Tm (-> formatted text buffers.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 465.50 Tm (- Control path: serial input is parsed non-blockingly; valid timestamps are normalized, written to the RTC, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 454.00 Tm (mirrored into system time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 442.50 Tm (- Repo note: README says `64x64` hardware, while `src/main.cpp` configures `32x32`; wiring diagram/service breakdown) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 431.00 Tm (beyond this is Not found in repo.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 411.50 Tm (How To Run) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 396.50 Tm (1. Open `D:\\DOKU\\##PlatformIO\\Projects\\myMatrixClock2` as a PlatformIO project.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 385.00 Tm (2. Use the checked-in `env:teensy31` target and connect the Teensy plus HUB75 matrix hardware.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 373.50 Tm (3. Build and upload the firmware from PlatformIO. Exact upload port/bootloader steps: Not found in repo.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 34.00 362.00 Tm (4. Open a 9600 baud serial monitor; after startup, send `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS` to set the RTC if needed.) Tj ET
